HEADWORD: Italianize
<hw>I*tal"ian*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Italianized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Italianizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
F. <ets>italianiser</ets>, It. <ets>italianizzare</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To play the Italian; to speak Italian.</def>
<rj><au>Cotgrave.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To render Italian in any respect; to
Italianate.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An Englishman <xex>Italianized</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

